{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"I assume this is for [THREE.UpdatableTexture](https:\/\/github.com\/spite\/THREE.UpdatableTexture)? Was this the only change you have to do?\r\n\r\nI've always seen `paramThreeToGL` as a hack so exposing doesn't feel good. Maybe that code could be modularised into something like `THREE.WebGLUtils`? Then you could instantiate that in your code.","created_at":"2017-07-26T15:58:08.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11846#issuecomment-318098799","id":318098799,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11846","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxODA5ODc5OQ==","updated_at":"2017-07-26T15:58:33.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/318098799","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Yes, that's just the change to be able to convert internal constants to GL constants, like in https:\/\/github.com\/spite\/THREE.UpdatableTexture\/blob\/master\/UpdatableTexture.js#L51\r\n\r\nWhat else could THREE.WebGLUtils provide? The whole function https:\/\/github.com\/spite\/three.js\/blob\/07239a245825a077347abef28c82dd27a81f75ea\/src\/renderers\/WebGLRenderer.js#L2472 could be a map, and I'm not sure, but may be you don't even need to reference the actual gl context, it can be any context. That would remove the dependency to renderer.paramThreeToGL, and just use THREE.convert or THREE.WebGLUtils.convert","created_at":"2017-07-26T16:05:43.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11846#issuecomment-318101335","id":318101335,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11846","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxODEwMTMzNQ==","updated_at":"2017-07-26T16:05:43.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/318101335","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/spite\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/spite\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/731885?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/spite","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/spite\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/spite","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/spite\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjczMTg4NQ==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/spite\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/spite\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/spite\/